reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good quality, a little too narrow
reviews.reviewText: I like the quality of the zippers, the fabric, the compression, the mesh, everything. What I don’t like is that the cubes are narrower than others I have. So I can’t fit as much in them because I have to fold or roll garments tighter than for my other brand. The zipper compression is great. I was able to put one pair of jeans, one pair of sweatpants, 2 knit tops, and one sweatshirt in the largest cube and compress it down. I could have fit mor without compressing.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great Set, but rather small
reviews.reviewText: I’ve used packing cubes for years and wouldn’t travel without them. Not only is it easier to keep different clothing articles sorted (I know exactly where to find a specific pair of pants, underwear or shirt), but when there is a shortage of drawer space, I can use the cubes to stay organized instead. On a recent cruise, we had upgraded to a better cabin, then were dismayed to realize it only had two drawers. By using my cubes, I was able to offer both of the drawers to my husband.So why did I need these? I’m really hoping to entice hubby into trying them and these aren’t in a feminine color. In addition to color, I like using cubes with a see-through panel, which these have. These even have a clear pocket on top of each to add a label to identify contents. I also like that these are compression cubes. I’ve traveled when my non-compression cubes were half filled and they generally got crumpled in my luggage during travel. The compression feature will be a nice upgrade.This set includes 7 bags as well as a small bag of empty bottles for lotions, shampoo, etc. Among the bags, there is a huge one for shoes (I could put two pair in here!) and another is a drawstring laundry bag that has an exterior pocket and even has straps to carry it as a backpack. While most of the bags have the mesh see-through panel, there is also one solid black bag, without the mesh, that has multiple compartments on the inside. Very handy!I’ll admit that when this set arrived, the small package felt unusually heavy, a big factor when staying under that 50 lb. limit when traveling by air. All of these bags together weigh 1.8lb, heavier than my old cubes probably because of the extra zippers, but it is rare that I would be using all 7 bags at once. I typically use one for pants, one for casual tops, one for dressier/dinner tops, and a smaller one for underwear/sleepwear/socks. So if my husband uses the other 2 or 3, the weight of the bags would be cut in half for each suitcase. Each cube has a handy little handle on the short side. On the negative side, these cubes are smaller than I’m accustomed to. With my old cubes, I’m able to fold my pants into thirds, which is the perfect width of the cube, then place two stacks of pants side by side. The largest of these cubes isn’t nearly large enough to do this. I’ll probably continue to use my old one for pants, then these new cubes for other items.I always try to offer some suggestion for improvement when leaving reviews. The only thing I’d recommend for these cubes would be to make the pull cords on the zippers different colors. I’d leave the primary zippers the existing gray color, but would make the compression zipper pulls black. This way, one could tell at a glance which was which. However, the primary zipper has two-way zippers so there are two gray pull-cords together. The compression zipper is a solo pull, so this is how I’ll be identifying which zipper does what. No real negative here, just trying to be thorough.Great cubes, but on the small size…Four Stars.I hope you found this review to be helpful. Thanks for reading!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars There is a Bag for Everything You Need to Pack
reviews.reviewText: There is a bag for everything you need to pack in this set. Even a bag for laundry. If you are easily confused by jet lag, you can even label the bags for contents as there are clear label pouches on most of the bags. The set is pretty and versatile. The zippers work smoothly and the garments and other bags are quality made.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great set of packing cubes
reviews.reviewText: I have been traveling with packing cubes for years now, and the compression style bags are by far my favorite. These are the best for storing and organizing your clothes without the extra bulk that comes with nature of folded clothes. My friend suggested that I roll my clothes instead of folding them with compression cubes. The theory is that you can compress a rolled shirt better than a folded shirt.These cubes are well designed, look good, and fit my luggage very well. There is an extra bonus of the label pocket and a stack of ready to go labels. If you're traveling for a long time, you can label your clothes by day, event, or category. I've found that this is extremely helpful for times when I'm attending a conference and want to keep certain outfits separated from the rest of my clothes.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Attractive, Innovative Space Savers
reviews.reviewText: These innovative travel cubes will be a great enhancement to your travel packing needs.The bags are smooth, attractive and made with easy to clean material. They are also a great value, with three standard cubes [small, medium and large], small and large duffle-type bags [for shoes and laundry] and another cube with internal pockets for unmentionables.The compression component works well to reduce space of folded items allowing more room in your luggage. The zippers and drawstring closures are made with quality and work easily. The netted portions of the cubes allow you to see the contents without opening the bags and there are even pockets sized perfectly for ID labels. The four TSA-approved containers are a nice added touch for an already great product package.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Not that special
reviews.reviewText: The bags aren't that big. Plus I can find very similar bags for less money. I just thought these bags would hold more because they're being advertised as these great compression bags. Wouldn't buy again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice quality packing cubes
reviews.reviewText: These seem to be made well. I’ll have to use them a few times to really be able to tell. On my initial use, they did great. The only thing I might want to see is that they included one that is a little larger for say, winter sweaters, light jackets, etc. that can be a little bulkier. But for undergarments, pajamas, tshirts, etc. these were wonderful. The travel size bottle set was great too, as well as the laundry backpack. All in all, a nice set.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars compression bags are great, the additional bags feel not quite necessary
reviews.reviewText: I like the compression bags. The labels are helpful to put on it, especially since you can't see what is inside very well due to the design. I was unsure that the compression element would help that much, but it really does! Now what I am going to do with all my old packing cubes from pre-2020 that don't have magic compression?I found the free travel size containers to feel like cheap plastic. I prefer my silicone ones I got at the store. I didn't really like the non-compression bags they threw in there for free, seemed more like an attempt to provide more products, but with less of a good effort at design.
